threats.title: Spoofing
threats.description: Spoofing is a cybercriminal activity where someone or something forges the sender's information and pretends to be a legitimate source.
threats.mitigation: Spoofing mitigations require a multi-layered approach that addresses specific vectors such as email, IP address, DNS, and ARP, combined with user education.
